                <div class="heading">Program Highlights:</div>
                <ul>
                    <li>Visual Communication Technology
                    <li>Project Lead the Way
                    <li>Five (5) Advanced Placement Classes – English, History, Biology, Calculus, Psychology
                    <li>Largest publicly accessible telescope in the Greater Delaware Valley
                    <li>Integrated media HDTV video studio
                    <li>Networking Essentials
                    <li>RET-Nano Technology (University of Pennsylvania and Drexel University)
                    <li>High-tech Media / Library Center with full video studio, computer labs, special education and resource center, counseling center, and before and after-care center.
                    <li>Peace Garden/Outside Classroom
                    <li>Awarded I3 ASSET grant and Environmental Education grant
                    <li>$500,000 in scholarships to 2011 graduating class
                    <li>Admissions include the University of Pennsylvania, Wharton, Drexel, MIT, Brown, Penn State, Temple, Villanova
                </ul>
                <div class="heading">Technology:</div>
                <ul>
                    <li>Promethean Boards/Smartboards in 65 classrooms
                    <li>13 sets of student response systems
                    <li>1230 computers in school
                    <li>Every teacher has a laptop that functions on the wireless network
                    <li>5 computers per classroom
                    <li>9 laptop carts of 15-30 computers
                    <li>9 active computer labs
                    <li>26 Elmo/document cameras
                    <li>Ratio per student: Approaching 1 to 1 (1,236 students)
                    <li>Over 80 different software programs running educationally in our environment
                    <li>Cisco based wireless network (38 access points) and Cisco Gigabit switching throughout
                    <li>Live Video Feed in all classrooms
                </ul>
                <div class="heading">Commendations:</div>
                <ul>
                    <li>Met 27/27 State AYP goals this year
                    <li>Adequate Yearly Progress for ten years
                    <li>2007 National Charter School of the Year by the U. S. Department of Education’s Center for Education Reform
                    <li>Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, House of Representatives Citation as an Outstanding Educational Facility
                    <li>2008 School District of Philadelphia Best Practice Partnership (with Parent Advisory Council)
                    <li>2009 PennFuture Award as a Green Building Leader
                    <li>2011 Top Ten Schools in Philadelphia by Philadelphia Magazine
                    <li>Tri-M Music Honor Society for Inspiring Music Participation and Leadership
                    <li>Philadelphia City Council for Providing State-of-the-Art Educational Opportunities
                    <li>2 National Merit Scholar Commended Students
                </ul>
        </section>
